    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade example of rotary engineering. The 13B-REW powerplant maintains factory-spec compression across all chambers, feeding through the original sequential twin-turbochargers for a seamless power band. The chassis remains rigid, featuring an unmolested double-wishbone suspension setup and the factory-correct Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line has been meticulously inspected to ensure the complex solenoid control system operates without hesitation. Finished in its original pigment with zero oxidation, this vehicle retains its perfect 50/50 weight distribution and legendary kinematic feedback. A concours-level specimen for the discerning collector.",
